review_text: Live music every Friday + Saturday 7pm, and we enjoyed the bands performance. Unfortunately they allowed indoor smoking, and with rather poor ventilation, it did smell smokey cigarette & went home with clothes smelling unpleasant smoke odour. Other than that, place itself was nice, comfy ambience. Service okay, servers were rather busy, place was packed full on weekend. Food itself, just average, nothin out of ordinary.
response_from_owner_text: Hi Pak Anthony, Terima kasih telah datang ke Intro Jazz dan memberikan pengalaman. Kami meminta maaf jika bapak dan keluarga tidak merasa nyaman dengan bau rokok yang tercium sampai di area non smoking. Untuk informasi,area smoking dan non smoking kami memang tidak dipisahkan jadi untuk bau rokok masih akan tercium dan meninggalkan bekas. Kami memohon maaf atas ketidaknyamanannya.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hi Mr Anthony, Thank you for coming to Intro Jazz and sharing your experience. We apologize if you and your family do not feel comfortable with the smell of cigarettes in the non-smoking area. For your information, our smoking and non-smoking areas are not separated so the smell of cigarettes will still be smelled and leave a mark. We apologize for the inconvenience.

review_text: A very attractive cafe, not too flashy from the outside but very spacious inside. When we came here on a weekday, there was no live music. Internet speed needs to be improved, the atmosphere is suitable for meetings with clients.

Great cafe for meeting and entertaint client. Casual business lunch mostly. I really enjoy tenderloin steak (buy 1 get 1) and margherita pizza. The magic coffee is good also. Great food, good service, nice place.  Would like to come again for dinner and enjoy jazz live music. Keep it up! Vegetarian options: Theres salad and vegan option food Parking: Free parking and a lot of spaces Wheelchair accessibility: Wheelchair friendly

review_text: Nice & cozy place with good foods. But they cost too high.

Saya merayakan Valentine dengan istri di sini. Promo 220rb untuk dua porsi Tenderloin 200gr, saya pilih sauce BBQ dan mushroom, keduanya medium rare. Dagingnya tebal tapi lembut. Sauce nya enak. Side nya fries dan buncis agak sedikit. Mushroom soupnya kental dan enak. Kopi marshmallow nya enak. Tempat cozy dan nyaman. Sayangnya antara smoking dan non smoking area tidak ada sekat. Saya terganggu dengan asap rokok, meski saya duduk di non smoking area.
review_translated_text: I celebrated Valentines with my wife here. Promo 220 thousand for two portions of 200g Tenderloin, I chose BBQ sauce and mushrooms, both medium rare. The flesh is thick but soft. The sauce is delicious. The sides are fries and a bit of green beans. The mushroom soup is thick and delicious. The marshmallow coffee is delicious. Cozy and comfortable place. Unfortunately, there is no partition between the smoking and non-smoking areas. I was bothered by cigarette smoke, even though I was sitting in a non-smoking area.

review_text: Roti nogat enak. Cream mokanya unik & di padu bumbu kacang.. Kalau fav saya sih yg 2 toping (meses & kacang).. Cm sayangnya roti ini kalo beli hrs d makan segera, kalau sdh ganti hari di makan lagi RASANYA KERAS DAN ALOT DI GIGIT..   cm kalau baru beli dan lgsng d makan - tdk smpe seharian.. enak banget & lembut.. Kmren sy coba panaskan pake oven 3 mnt sesuai anjuran & suhu normal. Tp malah jdnya kaya roti kering yg d jual di warung2, bkn kaya roti nogat yg lembutnya lagi.. Ya intinya enak d makan ketika baru jadi.. Lbh suka beli dr online, lbh murah & byk promo. Kalau beli lgsng ada pajaknya  lbh mahal beli di outlet menurut saya.. Tmpt nongkrongnya asik di lt2. Dingin & sepi..
review_translated_text: Delicious nogat bread. The mocha cream is unique & mixed with peanut sauce.. My favorite is the 2 toppings (meses & nuts).. Cm unfortunately, if you buy this bread you have to eat it immediately, if you eat it again the next day, IT TASTES HARD AND TOUGH TO BITE...   cm if you just buy it and eat it straight away - it wont last all day... its really delicious & soft... Yesterday I tried heating it using the oven for 3 minutes according to the recommendation & normal temperature. But instead it turns out like the dry bread that is sold in stalls, not like the soft nogat bread... Yes, the point is that its delicious to eat when its freshly made.. I prefer buying online, its cheaper & lots of promotions. If you buy directly there is a tax  its more expensive to buy at an outlet in my opinion... Its a cool place to hang out on the 2nd floor. Cold & quiet..

review_text: Iseng mampir karena pas lewat liat kok rame banget dan vibesnya juga sangat kekopian jadi sebagai coffee lover definitely ga boleh skip hahaha. Pas masuk wow tempatnya packed banget tapi ga pernah kosong pembeli, di depan juga rame yg duduk-duduk ngopi and this place even allows people to bring food from outside jadi emang sesantai itu. But apparently salah pesen menu karena kopi susunya way too acid, even buat penggemar arabica kayak gue ini terlalu asam. Untuk cappucinonya lebih enak, ternyata mereka beda beansnya. Berujung beli roasted beansnya mereka dan diservice juga dijelaskan dengan sangat baik. Penasaran pengen coba menu lain kalau ada kesempatan ke sini lagi, walau secara price-wise dia terbilang cukup tinggi ya dibanding coffee stall sejenis.
response_from_owner_text: Terima kaaih yah sudah mampir dan ditunggu kedatangan berikutnya. Oh iya, utk espresso based memang selalu ada 2 jenis beans yg setiap hari beda2, yg 1 diusahakan sebalance mungkin dan 1 lagi sesuai karakter asli beannya, next time boleh sambil ditanya ke crew baristanya yah.
review_translated_text: I just stopped by because when I passed by, it was really busy and the vibes were very coffeey, so as a coffee lover, you definitely cant skip it hahaha. When I entered, wow, the place was really packed but it was never empty of customers, there were lots of people sitting around drinking coffee at the front and this place even allowed people to bring food from outside so it was really that relaxing. But apparently I ordered the wrong menu because the coffee milk was way too acidic, even for Arabica fans like me, it was too sour. To make the cappuccino tastier, it turns out they have different beans. In the end, they bought roasted beans and the service was also explained very well. Im curious to try other menus if I have the opportunity to come here again, even though price-wise it is quite high compared to similar coffee stalls.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you for stopping by and waiting for your next arrival. Oh yes, for espresso based there are always 2 types of beans which are different every day, 1 which is tried to be as balanced as possible and 1 which matches the original character of the bean, next time you can ask the barista crew.

review_text: nyobain kopi Rosso the other day. varian yang saya coba: ice cappuccino using house blend beans (mixed arabica & robusta), ristretto. in term of taste cukup ok, as I expected, dalam artian ga mengecewakan, saya cukup suka dengan rasanya. tapi yang di Kasir nya, pas saya tanya-tanya untuk minta rekomendasi varian kopi, karena baru pertama kali ke sini, not helping at all. atau mungkin saya salah bertanya/minta rekomendasi, atau yang ke sini udah pasti tahu mau pesen apa, jadi tim Rosso yang melayani memang dipersiapkan untuk take order only tanpa dibekali kemampuan untuk memberikan rekomendasi? selain itu flopnya di packaging gelas plastiknya, jujur agak kecewa sih sama packaging nya, karena harga kopinya juga ga termasuk harga yang murah (paham, harga ini sepadan dengan kualitas beans kopinya), tapi boleh dong ya kasih masukan untuk gelas/packagingnya, karena kemarin itu belinya untuk take away. untuk harga segini, untuk packaging nya bisa lebih proper, terutama untuk bagian tutupnya. karena walaupun tutupnya udah diisolasi di bagian tempat nusuk sedotannya, tetap aja kopinya ada tumpah-tumpah dari pinggiran tutup nya. semoga next pas ke sini lagi, packaging nya udah lebih baik lagi. much success for Rosso.
response_from_owner_text: Halo kak Rini, terima kasih sebelumnya sudah meluangkan waktu untuk bisa menikmati sajian kopi di Rosso .... untuk masukan2nya juga bisa menjadikan koreksi serta perbaikan untuk mendatang, dan pastinya untuk kekurangan2nya kami minta maaf sebelumnya. Semoga nanti kak Rini saat kembali lagi, bisa mendapatkan insight yang lebih baik lagi, terutama untuk kopi2nya. Sukses & sehat selalu untuk kak Rini.
review_translated_text: try Rosso coffee the other day. variants I tried: ice cappuccino using house blend beans (mixed arabica & robusta), ristretto. in terms of taste its quite ok, as I expected, in the sense that it doesnt disappoint, I quite like the taste. but at the cashier, when I asked around to ask for recommendations on coffee variants, because it was my first time here, not helpful at all. Or maybe I asked the wrong question/asked for a recommendation, or do those who come here already know what they want to order, so the Rosso team serving is prepared to take orders only without being equipped with the ability to provide recommendations? Apart from that, the flop is in the plastic cup packaging, to be honest, Im a bit disappointed with the packaging, because the price of the coffee isnt cheap (understand, this price is commensurate with the quality of the coffee beans), but its okay, please give me input for the cup/ the packaging, because I bought it yesterday to take away. For this price, the packaging could be more appropriate, especially for the lid. because even though the lid has been isolated at the point where the straw is inserted, the coffee still spills out from the edge of the lid. Hopefully next time I come here, the packaging will be even better. much success for Rosso.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello Sis Rini, thank you in advance for taking the time to enjoy coffee at Rosso .... your input can also make corrections and improvements for the future, and of course for any shortcomings we apologize in advance. Hopefully when Sis Rini comes back, she can get better insight, especially regarding her coffee. Success & health always to Sis Rini.

review_translated_text: At first I was doubtful and also curious about the food. Many reviews say that the food is really delicious and are recommended to try. As for the location, from the front I was unsure. But when you enter, the interior is not bad, especially the toilet. The interior is eclectic with quite nice touches. The price of the food is quite pricey, but because Ive never tried Middle Eastern food before, maybe the price from my perspective isnt too relevant. As for the taste of the food, it turns out its true what the people in the review said. Very delicious! Their curry isnt too tasty, its not very strong, so its still safe to eat, but of course its creamy. Their hummus is really good. Ive never tried hummus before, I was afraid of not eating it because I was afraid it would taste bland or strange, but it turned out to be really delicious. Foods I tried at that time: - Zibba hummus (Delicious, the lamb has no smell, the meat is tender. But its better to share. Because of the creamy texture, if eaten alone, its definitely delicious) - Chicken Tikka Masala (the chicken is so tender, the curry is savory and really delicious, just right. Recommended! Just eat the curry with bread and its really delicious) Really had a good experience there, the staff was friendly and super nice.

review_text: Kesini karena bingung mau lunch di area BSD , dan cari referensi via tiktok. Ketemulah si Oddys ini. Kebetulan lokasi resto nya juga dekat sama tujuan kita selanjutnya. Jadi kita mampir lah kesini. Tempatnya lumayan oke yah, semi outdoor gitu dan ada ruangan AC nya, dan vibesnya menenangkan sih ya gak crowd sampe gimana2 jd makan jg tenang (kt kesini skitar pk 14.00-15.00), plus sepertinya bisa karoke deh disini. Yang bikin impressive sebenarnya sama pelayanannya sih. Semua waiter dan waitress yang melayani kita itu super duper ramah. Yes, seramah itu dan murah senyum pula.    Makanan juga cepet keluarnya dan panas2 juga. Menunya lumayan banyak ya: ada iga, nasi, western, dimsum, sampe gelato juga ada. Lumayan lama buat milih2 mau makan apa. Dan setelah liat menu. Kita putusin buat pesen Sego Campur cumi tinta dan sego Ayam Lodho. Cukup enak untuk keduanya, baik cumi dan Ayam lodhonya. Kuah lodhonya enak, sambalnya jg nyaman dimakan (gak sampe kepedesan gt) jadi seperti makan ketupat / opor teksturnya. nasinya jg disajikan anget2 cocok sih berasa makan menu rumahan. Kita jg ada pesan cireng, awalnya terlihat kok oily banget ya.. tapi ternyata nggak kok, saus kecap nya rasa rujak2 gt enak. Dan di goreng dengan matang ya sampe kriuk. Overall buat first timer kesini, ini tempat yang nice sih. Cm saran aja mungkin yang indoor dikasih penerangan lbh terang yah/ mungkin perangkap nyamuk.  krn kita sempat digigitin nyamuk, walaupun gak signifikan ya . Untuk harga worth it sekali ya. Makan kenyang harga sesuai kantong untuk tempat seperti ini Thanks Oddys for filled our tummy
review_translated_text: Came here because I was confused about whether to have lunch in the BSD area, and looked for references via TikTok. Meet Oddys. Coincidentally, the location of the restaurant is also close to our next destination. So we stopped by here. The place is pretty good, its semi-outdoor and theres an AC room, and the vibes are calming, there arent too many crowds, so eating is also calm (we come here around 14.00-15.00), plus it looks like you can do karoke here. What makes it impressive is actually the service. All the waiters and waitresses who served us were super duper friendly. Yes, that friendly and smiling too.    The food also comes out quickly and is hot too. The menu is quite extensive: there are ribs, rice, western, dimsum, even gelato. It takes quite a long time to choose what to eat. And after looking at the menu. We decided to order Sego Mix squid ink and Lodho Chicken sego. Quite delicious for both, both the squid and the lodho chicken. The lodho sauce is delicious, the chili sauce is also comfortable to eat (its not too spicy) so its like eating ketupat/opor in texture. The rice is also served hot, which makes it feel like youre eating a home-cooked meal. We also ordered cireng, at first it looked really oily... but it turned out not to be, the soy sauce sauce tasted like rujak2, it was really delicious. And fried thoroughly until crispy. Overall, for first timers here, this is a nice place. Just a suggestion, maybe give the indoor ones brighter lighting, maybe a mosquito trap. because we were bitten by mosquitoes, although it wasnt significant. For the price, its really worth it. Full meal at pocket-friendly prices for a place like this Thanks Oddys for filling our tummy

review_text: Review berdasarkan kunjungan kami di tanggal 9 September  2023. Kami memesan mix pork rice Dan fish n chips. Mix pork rice nya cukup enak, nasi nya hambar, tertolong kalau dituang kecap pelengkap nya, sajian topping daging pork nya cukup mengenyangkan. Kuah kaldu yang diberikan kurang berguna, hanya seperti air diberi lada. Fish n chips nya kurang memuaskan. Bentuk fish nya gendut-gendut seperti pisang molen, hanya tebal di tepung saja dan hambar. Kentang goreng nya lebih lumayan karena menggunakan merek kentang yang sudah coated, sehingga garing nya pas. Overall untuk harga dan rasa nya, fish n chips nya sangat tidak kami rekomendasikan. Parking: Parkir di area parkir Mall The Breeze Wheelchair accessibility: Ada 2 anak tangga untuk masuk ke Restoran. Kursi roda harus diangkat.
review_translated_text: Review based on our visit on September 9, 2023. We ordered mix pork rice and fish n chips. The mixed pork rice is quite delicious, the rice is bland, it helps if you add the complementary soy sauce, the pork topping is quite filling. The broth that is given is not useful, its just like water with pepper. The fish n chips were not satisfying. The shape of the fish is fat like banana molen, only thick in flour and tasteless. The fries are better because they use a brand of coated potatoes, so they are just right. Overall, for the price and taste, we really dont recommend the fish n chips. Parking: Park in The Breeze Mall parking area Wheelchair accessibility: There are 2 stairs to enter the restaurant. The wheelchair must be lifted.

Cuma saya kurang cocok sama nasi goreng yg pake nanas. Saya lebih suka yg gurih. Oh, ya, ada semacam teh rempah yg unik--love potion--yg diminum di cangkir yg superimut. Uang yg saya keluarkan beda2 jumlahnya karena saya juga pesannya beda2.
review_translated_text: The place is okay and instagrammable. The atmosphere is fun with background music. The food and drinks are delicious. Ive been here 3 times. First, when the cafe just opened. It was dinner time with friends. The atmosphere is lively. Second, at the end of last year I had coffee with friends in the afternoon. The atmosphere is quiet. Third, earlier this month I had lunch with friends from Jakarta. Quite busy. I just dont like fried rice that uses pineapple. I prefer savory ones. Oh, yes, there is a unique kind of spiced tea--love potion--which is drunk in super cute cups. The amount of money I spent was different because I also ordered different amounts.

review_text: Coffe lokasi strategis biasa sore pulang kantor sekedar meeting kecil atau hanya rehat. Rasa coffee standar, rekomendasi macha dan makanan kecil ubi. review_translated_text: Coffee in a strategic location, usually in the afternoon after work for a small meeting or just taking a break. Standard coffee taste, recommended macha and sweet potato snacks. The atmosphere can be while watching the traffic while doing homework. The ablution and prayer room is available on the 2nd floor, the bathroom is quite clean. Parking is also still free. Close to home so you can go directly to a gojek/gocar. The place is comfortable enough to work and can be close to an electrical contact for charging the laptop. Usually in the afternoon and evening the atmosphere is dynamic with views of the Kencana Loka T-junction.

review_text: Been here couole weeks ago. The setting was nice but some part is to dark (round table next to sofa). Ordered pizza, cream based pasta and ravioli. The pizza is good. The dough and the toppings is nice. But im so sorry to say to the management that your pasta sauce and ravioli bit watery. The taste is a okay well the cream overpowered all but its a shame when you had a watery sauce pasta. Maybe the cook in a hurry or maybe thats the standard recipe. But please management if you see this check how was your cream pasta sauce done. Oh and one more we ordered fried mozarella stick. Its nice but to greasy or oily in my opinion. The texture is nice we got the gooey cheese inside, kids love it. Spacious parking spot and also hey they got good deal promotion though...
response_from_owner_text: Dear porq99, when we are receiving feedback like yours, we are taking it very serious and we do check our Operations before we answer. We found out, that your pasta dishes were indeed not prepared according to our instructions. This is, because at that time we had a new Chef at our outlet and obviously he missed an important part of his extensive briefing. We already trained him again to make sure, that in the future our dishes are prepared in the right way. Regarding the Mozzarella sticks: as with all fried stuff there is a trade off between bring it hot to the table vs. leave it on the kitchen tissue to soak out all oil. I guess we were a bit fast in your case... But Im happy to read that your kids liked it. This explanation does not make your experience at our restaurant undone, but we hope you do see that we are are committed to continuously improving the quality of our service and food. To you we apologize for the shortcomings in your dining experience ! We value your visits at our restaurant and want to ensure that you have a positive experience every time you visit us. Kind Regards, Sven Team john & james

5555555/5!!! cafe yg sangat cocok utk cat lovers! pintu pertama (area utk food processing) sangat amat bersih! saya suka banget! sptnya memang area steril krn utk buat makanan, makanya kucing2 gaboleh di area itu. lalu masuk lagi pintu kedua (area kucing,area makan) lgsg  brengg  mulai kerasa bau kucingnya  mungkin utk orang yg gak terbiasa pelihara kucing akan merasa terganggu, tp saya pun cat owner jd maklum kalau bau ruangannya spt itu, bau khas kucing. oke utk ordernya ada minimal per guest harus 2 order menu (makan minum). saya order kopi dan bbrp cemilan. rasanya oke, enak2 bgt, tidak ngasal. ada merchandise kucing juga lucu2 bgt! oiya, yg saya suka juga yaitu pelayanannya yaampunn mba di sana ramah2 semua    kami dilayani dg sgt baik utk kucingnya banyak benar2 terawat, gemuk2, bersih2, dan gak takut orang. hny saja sulit utk digendong jd cuma bisa dielus2 aja, kadang utk difoto pun sulit krn kabur2an, dan malas utk diajak bermain saya paling suka sama Lili dan Frosty yaampunn mereka itu gemes bgt! Recommended cafe! 1000000/10
review_translated_text: 5555555/5!!! A very suitable cafe for cat lovers! The first door (the area for food processing) is very, very clean! I really like it! It seems like the area is sterile because it is for making food, so cats are not allowed in that area. then enter the second door again (cat area, eating area) and immediately brengg I start to feel the smell of cats  maybe for people who are not used to keeping cats it will feel disturbed, but I am also a cat owner so I understand that the room smells like that, a typical cat smell. OK, for orders, there is a minimum per guest of 2 menu orders (food and drink). I ordered coffee and some snacks. the taste is okay, really delicious, not unpleasant. Theres really cute cat merchandise too! Oh yes, what I also like is the service, ladies and gentlemen there, everyone is friendly    we were served really well for many cats, they are really well looked after, fat, clean, and not afraid of people. Its just difficult to carry  so you can only stroke it, sometimes its difficult to take photos because you run around, and youre too lazy to play with I really like Lili and Frosty, oh my gosh, they are so cute! Recommended cafe! 1000000/10

review_translated_text: The place is in an apartment and there is no special entrance fee, but you must order one meal and one drink. The cats are well-groomed, dont smell, and are all well-groomed. You must wash your hands before entering and can directly interact with the cat.

review_text: Nice place, adorable cats. Kucingnya bersih dan gendut. Datang di weekday tempatnya sepi, bersih, nyaman dan tidak bau. Toilet bersih. Makanan enak, harga agak pricey tp ok lah. Banyak mainan kucing bagi yg ingin bermain dengan kucing.
review_translated_text: Nice place, adorable cats. The cat is clean and fat. Come on a weekday, the place is quiet, clean, comfortable and doesnt smell. Clean toilets. The food is delicious, the price is a bit pricey but its ok. Lots of cat toys for those who want to play with cats.

review_text: Cafe kucing yang proper. Tempatnya nyaman dan kucingnya terawat. Makanannya juga oke. Kemaren nyobain semacam japanese hamburg gitu. Lokasinya mudah dijangkau dari Stasiun Serpong ataupun Rawabuntu.
review_translated_text: A proper cat cafe. The place is comfortable and the cats are well looked after. The food is also okay. Yesterday I tried something like Japanese Hamburger. The location is easy to reach from Serpong or Rawabuntu Station.

review_text: Its a great place if you are cat lover, as all the cat is adorable. Food wise i will say its standard, nothing special as the highlight is chill with cat as the theme. To be note the spicy food here is spicy as it is use cut of real chilli instead of powder.
came for the cats, stayed for the cats. the food is pretty decent too & well priced, knowing you dont need to pay fees for the entrance.

Cozy cat cafe situated in a concrete jungle. Upon stepping in, we were greeted by numerous cats, which roamed around the cafe. They have different personalities: careful, playful, standoffish, and mostly curious, not to mention clever. Food options were decently priced, while their drinks were unique - we particularly enjoyed the sakura coffee. No entry fee required. We were also allowed to wear our shoes into the cafe. First time visiting a cat cafe - it was overall a pleasant experience: 4 out of 5.

review_translated_text: On Saturday-Sunday, the time was limited to 1 hour and they were told to go out, so I was not satisfied, the service from the cashier was also not friendly to non-hijab people.

review_text: Datang langsung pesan, min. order 2 items/orang. Banyak merchandise lucu yg dijual. Kebetulan datang pas anabul meal-time dan pemandangan buntelan bulu terpampang jelas

review_text: Datang ke sini karena anak-anak suka sekali dengan kucing. Pintu masuknya tidak langsung menuju tempat makan dengan kucing, melainkan ke meja kasir dan toko souvenir. Saya suka desain seperti itu karena jadi menjaga keamanan kucing dan memastikan kucing tidak bisa kabur setiap pintu dibuka. Menunya juga enak-enak, kami pesan beberapa menu berupa pasta, nasi goreng, dan australian beef teriyaki. Enak-enak semua, anak-anak doyan. Tapi hati hati ya, soalnya ada kucing yang masih belum tuntas toilet trainingnya. Sepatu anak saya sempat dikencingi kucing selagi anak-anak menikmati makanan di tempat lesehan. Oiya, namanya coffice, karena perpaduan coffee dan office. Jadi emang cozy dan cocok banget untuk bekerja, WFC cenah.
review_translated_text: Came here because the children really like cats. The entrance does not lead directly to the dining area with cats, but to the cashiers desk and souvenir shop. I like this design because it keeps the cat safe and ensures the cat cant escape every time the door is opened. The menu was also delicious, we ordered several menus in the form of pasta, fried rice and Australian beef teriyaki. Its all delicious, the kids love it. But be careful, because there are cats that still havent completed their toilet training. My childs shoes were peed on by a cat while the children were enjoying food on the floor. Oh yes, its called coffice, because its a combination of coffee and office. So its really cozy and really suitable for work, WFC is light.

review_text: Cats lover heaven! You have to order at least 2 items to get in with a 1 hour time limit. The coffee is ok, they have some cute cookies and cat themed goodies. Great selection of foods from snacks - heavy meal. Ordered their Calicomurice and sakura tea. It was pretty good. Would come back again for the cats! Parking: Narrow parking space

review_translated_text: Vegan restaurant!! It is located not far from the entrance gate towards the breeze. Burgreens allows us to bring pets. You can order by grab. The taste of the food is also delicious. Yes of course please dont compare with real food. But for people who are used to vegan food, you will definitely like it. But not all of the menu is delicious. The first time I came here I ordered crunchy salad with chicken. Nice. But you cant deny that the chicken has to be dipped in sauce to make it delicious. Then I also ordered boba brown sugar milk tea so yummy. The second visit was a bit disappointed, ordered the creamy truffle pasta - it honestly tasted delicious like the pasta I cook myself at home. I ordered a burger and it didnt taste good, the plant based burger was FORE  . My husband ordered yellow rice rendang with tempe satay - this was delicious. Oh yes, there arent many choices of fresh drinks

review_text: Paul seemingly doesnt care so much any more. Came here for breakfast and got some disappointment the whole way. The service was ok, waiters a little slow but kind of friendly. But the food!!! 100k++ for a sandwich with dry, yes dry salad leaves and a thin like paper thin slice of tomato, which has seen better days two weeks ago. The bread hard like a cookie. They were lucky that we were starving. Otherwise, we would have left straight away. When we wanted to leave it took a good while for the waiters to realise. So in summary: The coffee was ok, so if someone wants to come for coffee and stay for hours without being bothered by a waiter, it might be a good place to go if you bring your own cleaning products to clean your table by yourself as the waiters didnt care much.

Overall service was good, the waitress was very supportive and kind, food was ok, relatively pricey but ok. I ordered spaghetti pesto with chicken breast, the chicken was yummy. Also ordered herbal tea and it was good. Special shout out to the waitress, we were staying till it closure time and asked help to take many pictures. And she was very patiently and happily assisting us (and the photo she took was also good, she told us which spot is better etc? Happy with the experience and will be back

review_text: Dont get me wrong by seeing the bad review. The service is good, the waitresses are really helpful. But the food is MAJOR disappointment. Seriously, make better food or just stick to pastry. Drinks are good. Pastry is good. Mushroom soup was INCREDIBLY salty. Im not exaggerating here, it was like eating salt with soup. Fortunately they apologized and took mine back and served another one which was ok. But it did not impress. Pasta did not impress. It was ok, but not the taste I was hoping for, for the price that I paid. I can find lots of other restaurants that serve way better pasta for that price level in BSD. Then came the Atlantic sandwich. It was DANGEROUSLY SALTY. I was not the only one who tasted and complained. We ate half, couldnt finish it, didnt want to risk our health. I paid the bill, which was 500k++, still hungry, disappointed, with a tinge of stinging saltiness in my mouth. We commented that food was not ok and was too salty, they mentioned that it came that way from the supplier. Well, do better! I cant believe youre THE paul le cafe from France. My dinner was ruined here. Seriously, FIX IT.

I like the croissants that I bought, it really taste like it was made with premium ingredients. It was 8 in the morning and they had only a few customers but it took some times to heat up my croissant. Other than that the staff and atmosphere was nice.

I recently visited Paul Bakery at The Breeze with my family for breakfast. After strolling around the area, we decided to stop by and try their offerings. We ordered a hot cappuccino, continental breakfast, a plain croissant, and a chocolate croffle. While the food was decent, it didnt particularly stand out or have any unique flavors. It was just okay, nothing remarkable. However, I must say that the service we received was excellent. The staff was attentive and friendly, ensuring we had a pleasant experience. Additionally, the ambiance of the bakery was lovely, creating a nice atmosphere to enjoy our meal. Overall, my visit to Paul Bakery at The Breeze was satisfactory. The food was average, but the outstanding service and pleasant ambiance made up for it

Something rare in Serpong! A homey coffeeshop with kids corner Situated in Griya Loka area, this coffeeshop is cozy. In our opinion, its laptopable on the first floor and family-friendly on the second floor (with kids corner here). They serve coffee, non-coffee, snack, main course and dessert. Most of the food served here is asian food. Recommended menu: - Hot Cappuccino using full arabica blend Brazil and Argopuro. Overall its sweet! - Double Prime. A milk coffee using another milk coffee ice cube. Making it not watery, thick, creamy and sweet while maintaining the coffee taste. - Strawberry Chezzy Cream. Cheesy, creamy and taste like candy (sugus-like!). - Nasi Kari Ayam Crispy. Crispy katsu with Japanese curry (slightly spicy). Tasty! - Yamien Baso (there are 2 options; savory or sweet. We chose sweet.) Turns out, not as sweet as we thought. The noodle is well-cooked and we like the meatball! - Siomay. Love this!! Soft, we can still taste the fish (so not too much flour in it) but not fishy. If youre looking for a place to hangout with friends while bringing your kids, try this!!

Travelers, lagi nyari tempat ngopi yang suasanya tenang dan kids Friendly? Mampir yuk ke Bluperry Coffee Design interiornya dengan warna warni khas ala Santorini. Bagus banget. Ada 3 lantai. Lantai 1 indoor dan outdoor area dan digabung sama bar & kitchen. Lantai 2 indoor dan outdoor area, kids corner, smooking area Lantai 3 khusus untuk toilet dan mushola Pelayanan dari barista yang ramah, tempatnya bersih, dan WFC able. Kebanyakan customer disini tuh kalo pagi ada Mommy yang abis nganter anaknya sekolah sambil nunggu dan ada juga mommy yang langsung WFC disini karena lokasinya dekat sama beberapa sekolahan. Sorenya ada beberapa kawula muda sampai malam hari. Untuk menunya bervariatif banget. Dan menurut aku ini salah satu cafe yang nyediain menu enak-enak dengan harga yang affordable. Aku cobain beberapa menu : Espresso Based : Affogato (4/5) Moctails : Lady in Black (5/5) ini best seller disini. Mixed berries dengan signature kopi arabica Tea House : Lychee Tea (4/5) Starters : Korean Spicy Bluperry Chicken Wings (5/5) Main course Asian : Nasi Liwet Cakalang (5/5) Pasta & Western : Spaghetti carbonara (5/5) Dessert : Banana French Toast with Vanilla Ice Cream (5/5) Travelers, kalo lagi ada di daerah BSD jangan lupa mampir ya ke Bluperry Coffee. Lokasinya gak terlalu jauh dari Stasiun Commuterline Rawa Buntu.
review_translated_text: Travelers, looking for a place to drink coffee that is calm and kid friendly? Lets stop by at Bluperry Coffee The interior design is colorful, typical of Santorini style. Really good. There are 3 floors. The 1st floor is an indoor and outdoor area and is combined with a bar & kitchen. 2nd floor indoor and outdoor areas, kids corner, smoking area The 3rd floor is specifically for toilets and prayer rooms Friendly service from the barista, the place is clean, and WFC capable. Most of the customers here in the morning are mothers who have dropped off their children at school while waiting and there are also mothers who directly WFC here because the location is close to several schools. In the afternoon there were several young people until evening. The menu is very varied. And in my opinion, this is one of the cafes that provides delicious menus at affordable prices. I tried several menus: Espresso Based : Affogato (4/5) Moctails: Lady in Black (5/5) is the best seller here. Mixed berries with signature Arabica coffee Tea House : Lychee Tea (4/5) Starters : Korean Spicy Bluperry Chicken Wings (5/5) Main course Asian : Nasi Liwet Cakalang (5/5) Pasta & Western : Spaghetti carbonara (5/5) Dessert : Banana French Toast with Vanilla Ice Cream (5/5) Travelers, if youre in the BSD area, dont forget to stop by Bluperry Coffee. The location is not too far from Rawa Buntu Commuterline Station.

review_text: Cute little Japanese Cafe hideen in midst of BSD. Nearly everything we had was spot on - edamame was steamed well (not overcooked), grilled corn was crunchy, and my katsu curry was ever so tasty. The only small fault was the gyoza, where it was still cold on the inside and didnt have the right texture nor bite. That said, this place still rocks. The matcha used is authentic and packs a punch, exemplified by the matcha cheesecake (reminds me on Tsujiri in London or Melbourne). Love the attentive service and the interior aesthetics. Come for the drinks, but should try the delightful food.

review_text: Definitely will recommend this place! Service & Suasana: - Pelayannya ramah banget, helpful juga kalo ditanya rekomendasi - Suasananya jejepangan gitu unik, sampe playlistnya juga Jepang semua deh kayaknya (aku pribadi kurang suka ini hehe) - Ada banyak pilihan board game, beberapa bisa untuk anak-anak juga - Sangat enak juga buat WFC karena tempat duduknya nyaman untuk berjam-jam, banyak stop kontak, dan wifinya stabil - Sedihnya ga ada musola di sini Makanan - Matcha Parfait (9/10): Enak, kombinasinya unik ada kacang merah, cornflakes, jelly, dan mochinya gitu, semuanya seger & matcha di eskrimnya berasa - Matcha Cheesecake (9/10): Ini cheesecake berwarna hijau aja menurutku, matchanya ga berasa sama sekali, tapi secara rasa enakk!!! Burntnya juga mantep - Berry Matcha Latte (8/10): Kayak kurang blend gitu rasa matcha & blueberrynya, kalo diaduk rasanya akan lebih ke matcha, terus di akhir2 rasanya akan sangat berry karena mengendap gitu berrynya, tapi overall rasanya enak-enak aja - Katsu curry rice (7.5/10): Not my yum curry taste, bingung deskripsiinnya tapi intinya rasa karinya bukan rasa yang aku suka aja sih

review_translated_text: Definitely will recommend this place! Service & Atmosphere: - The waiters are very friendly, also helpful when asked for recommendations - The Japanese atmosphere is so unique, even the playlist is all Japanese, I think (I personally dont like this hehe) - There is a large selection of board games, some for children too - Its also very good for WFC because the seating is comfortable for hours, lots of sockets, and the wifi is stable - Sadly there is no prayer room here Food - Matcha Parfait (9/10): Delicious, unique combination of red beans, cornflakes, jelly and mochi, everything is fresh & the matcha in the ice cream tastes good - Matcha Cheesecake (9/10): This is just a green cheesecake in my opinion, the matcha doesnt taste at all, but the taste is delicious!!! The burnt is also steady - Berry Matcha Latte (8/10): It seems like the matcha & blueberry flavor isnt quite blended, if you stir it the taste will be more matcha, then at the end the taste will be very berry because the berries settle in, but overall the taste is just fine - Katsu curry rice (7.5/10): Not my yum curry taste, confused about the description but basically the curry taste is not the taste that I just like

review_translated_text: Carrying the Matcha Cafe concept, you can see from the interior design that the concept is very Japanese, from the wooden accents to the chairs and glass. On the second floor there are board games and comic books, making the cafe atmosphere seem more homey. The matcha cheese cake is delicious, the portion is also generous, you can share it together. Almond Croissants are also crunchy and buttery. The coffee is made with cinnamon, which personally doesnt suit me. We also tried the food but forgot to take photos. The hamburger is delicious, for me the oyako don is not suitable because it uses floury chicken katsu meat and doesnt have a lot of eggs. Overall delicious, I will come back for the cake and pastry. Kid-friendliness: There are board games and comic books

review_text: Berada dibilangan daerah BSD dekat Granada, dimana banyak sekali kuliner dipinggir jalan. Untuk tempatnya sendiri berada di teras rumah sangat terbatas dan kurang nyaman menurut saya, dimana hanya terdapat 2 meja memanjang, selebihnya hanya ada 4 meja lesehan tanpa alas. Saya yang saat itu sedang hamil besar sangat-sangat tidak nyaman dengan tempatnya. Untuk pilihan menunya sendiri cukup bervariatif mulai dari minuman tradisional rempah hangat hingga minuman tradisional dingin. Untuk harga sendiri sangat ramah dikantong. Menu makanan camilannya juga variatif, ada nasi bakar dengan porsi nasi kucing dengan rasa isi cumi dan teri yg enak, saya suka uli bakarnya. Ada sate-satean dan bakwan goreng yg dibuat dadakan. Oiya, ada kacang tanah goreng yg menurut saya enak.
review_translated_text: Its in the BSD area near Granada, where there are lots of culinary delights on the side of the road. In my opinion, the place itself is on the terrace of the house, it is very limited and not very comfortable, where there are only 2 long tables, the rest there are only 4 floor-to-ceiling tables without mats. I, who was very pregnant at that time, was very, very uncomfortable with the place. The menu choices themselves are quite varied, ranging from traditional warm spiced drinks to traditional cold drinks. The price itself is very pocket friendly. The snack menu is also varied, there is grilled rice with a portion of cat rice filled with delicious squid and anchovies, I like the grilled uli rice. There are satays and fried bakwan which are made impromptu. Oh yes, there are fried peanuts which I think are delicious.

review_text: 1. Lokasi dekat Bahkmi Jowo Mbah Putri ternyata. Sorry, rada2 salfok! 2. Mas yg jual nih ngeracik wedang rempah nya mantap banget! Walaupun dadakan ngeracik pake numbuk2 rempah, pas diminum tuh rasanya enak, manisnya pas, dan rempahnya berasa. 3. Ada Ketan Bakar juga. Nikmat bgt! 4. Really recommended, terlebih sangat dianjurkan untuk menambah imunitas dan kesehatan lho! Note: Mau nambahin bbrp hal kalo ke sini: - Kudu sabar, karena bikin nya agak lama. Kyk tahu bulat digoreng dadakan, demikian jg ini wedang, dibuat nya dadakan pula. Sudah itu pula, racik dan rebus air rempahnya pake pemanas listrik yg buat kopi, cuma bisa buat 3 gelas / teko. - Dekmikian juga pas bakar ketan jg lama, kyk nya bukan yg pake arang. - Tempat terbatas: kursi depan gerobak, bbrp meja lesehan, 1 meja panjang.
review_translated_text: 1. The location is apparently near Bahkmi Jowo Mbah Putri. Sorry, a bit confused! 2. The guy who sells this makes really good spiced wedang! Even though I suddenly mixed it up using a bunch of spices, when I drank it, it tasted delicious, the sweetness was just right, and the spices were delicious. 3. There is grilled sticky rice too. So delicious! 4. Really recommended, especially highly recommended to increase immunity and health, you know! Note: I want to add a few things if I come here: - You have to be patient, because it takes a while to make. Like round tofu fried impromptu, so is this wedang, made impromptu too. After that, mix and boil the spiced water using an electric heater that makes coffee, it can only make 3 cups/pot. - Likewise, when you burn sticky rice for a long time, it doesnt look like you use charcoal. - Limited space: chairs in front of the cart, several lesehan tables, 1 long table.

BARU TAU kalo di Babah Ramu punya menu kopi dan pastries/breads   Selama ini, mimin kira sedia makanan berat aja Kopi yang mereka pake blend 40% Arabica dan 60% Robusta dari roemahkoffie. Jadi untuk Hot Cappuccino dan Hot Latte yang kami coba, memang sedikit pait. Lebih enak di flavored latte, kami coba Iced Vanilla Latte. Pastry dan breadnya freshly baked setiap hari; kami coba Butter Croissant, Pain Au Chocolat, Coffee Bun dan Sausage Mayo yang jadi special menu hari ini. Semua pastry mereka full butter dan menurut kami  enak kok, ngga terlalu manis dan butternya juga ngga overwhelming banget. Btw, yang bikin mimin kaget adalah harga pastry nya ini antara 25-35k tapi ukurannya gedeee bangettt _____ Visited by #NgopiDiSerpong team in August 2023. Follow us on IG/TT/THRD: @ngopidiserpong
review_translated_text: JUST KNOW that Babah Ramu has a menu of coffee and pastries/breads   So far, I thought only heavy food was available The coffee they use is a blend of 40% Arabica and 60% Robusta from Roemahkoffie. So the Hot Cappuccino and Hot Latte that we tried were a bit bitter. Its better in a flavored latte, we tried the Iced Vanilla Latte. The pastry and bread are freshly baked every day; We tried Butter Croissant, Pain Au Chocolat, Coffee Bun and Sausage Mayo which were todays special menu. All of their pastries are full of butter and we think theyre delicious, not too sweet and the butter isnt too overwhelming either. BTW, what surprised me was that the price of this pastry is between 25-35k but the size is really big _____ Visited by #NgopiDiSerpong team in August 2023. Follow us on IG/TT/THRD: @ngopidiserpong

Ketika saya datang pertama kali, saya disambut dengan aroma harum saus yang sangat lezat. Awalnya saya datang karena menemani teman saya, namun karena aromanya yang sangat lezat, saya akhirnya memesan juga. Dan ternyata benar, sate paha yang manis sangat lezat, tidak pernah saya makan ayam selembut dan seempuk ini. Ditambah lagi minuman free refill dan juga harga yang murah membuat saya sekarang tertagih untuk makan disini. Selain dari itu staff mereka juga sangat baik (shoutout kepada Billy dan Laksmi), serta penyajian yang cepat dan bersih. Dari pengalaman ini saya rate restaurant ini 5/5 dari segala sisi.
review_translated_text: When I first came, I was greeted with the fragrant aroma of a very delicious sauce. Initially I came because I was accompanying my friend, but because the aroma was so delicious, I finally ordered too. And it turned out to be true, the sweet thigh satay was very delicious, I have never eaten chicken as soft and tender as this. Plus the free refill drinks and cheap prices make me want to eat here now. Apart from that, their staff is also very good (shoutout to Billy and Laksmi), and the serving is fast and clean. From this experience, I rate this restaurant 5/5 from all sides.

Exquisite Chinese Cuisine with Exceptional Service at Restoran Central Serpong I recently had the pleasure of dining at Restoran Centrals Serpong branch, and the experience left me thoroughly impressed. This Chinese restaurant not only boasts a diverse menu but also delivers on taste with every dish, leaving no room for disappointment. Having harbored a long-standing interest in trying out Restoran Central Serpong, fueled by my previous satisfying experience at their Tomang branch in Jakarta, my expectations were high, and Im pleased to say they were exceeded. The culinary offerings span a variety of Chinese delicacies, each expertly crafted to perfection. From the first bite to the last, every dish on the menu is a flavorful journey that showcases the culinary expertise of the chefs at Restoran Central. Its safe to say that theyve mastered the art of Chinese cuisine. What sets Restoran Central apart is not just the delectable food but also the impeccable service that accompanies it. The staff exudes a level of professionalism that reflects the establishments commitment to excellence. The service is attentive, prompt, and truly elevates the overall dining experience. Its evident that the restaurant takes pride in offering a dining atmosphere that goes beyond just the food. While the prices may lean towards the higher side, they are undoubtedly justified by the exquisite flavors and top-notch service. Restoran Central Serpong doesnt just sell a meal; it sells an experience, and in this case, its an experience worth every penny. For those looking to host special events, Restoran Central Serpong provides a VIP room capable of accommodating around 100 guests. This feature adds another layer of versatility to the restaurant, making it an ideal choice for celebrations and gatherings. Conveniently, parking is available right in front of the restaurant, eliminating any hassle for patrons. The ease of access only adds to the overall positive impression I had during my visit. In conclusion, Restoran Central Serpong is a gem for Chinese cuisine enthusiasts. The combination of delectable dishes, impeccable service, and thoughtful amenities make it a dining destination worth considering, even with the relatively higher prices. If youre seeking an upscale Chinese dining experience in Serpong, Restoran Central should be at the top of your list.

Karena tidak menjawab pertanyaan saya, saya ulang lagi pertanyaan saya jadi ada atau tidak? Baru staff menjawab ada kak tapi berisik tanpa menunjukkan dan mengantarkan saya ke lokasi meja yg kosong untuk saya lihat terlebih dahulu. Karena respon yang seperti menolak dengan halus, saya cancel saja better cari cafe lain. Harusnya ditraining ya staffnya bagaimana handle customer dan mungkin dibuat SOP waiting list jika memang kondisi sedang ramai.
review_translated_text: This cafe doesnt have a waiting list or training system for employees or what? The service is a bit lacking and seems arrogant and doesnt want to accept guests. So I went in and the staff inside asked how many people, then I answered for two people but the response was like the following under full sis, Then I asked again what about upstairs?, the staff then answered its noisy upstairs, sis, theres a social gathering. Because it didnt answer my question, I repeated my question again so its there or not? Only then did the staff answer its there, but its noisy without showing me and taking me to an empty table for me to look at first. Because the response seemed like a gentle refusal, I just canceled and better look for another cafe. The staff should be trained on how to handle customers and perhaps create a waiting list SOP if conditions are busy.

Meanwhile, on the 2nd floor there is a full dining area and there is 1 private room / smoking room The food menu is also unique, unfortunately some of the menus are already sold out because maybe I came a little late. review_translated_text: While Im swimming at Ocean Park BSD, take a look at the cafe which is really popular in BSD. On Sunday afternoon, around 2pm, there were still 7 queues. I sat down around half past midnight. While waiting to see the menu, maybe you can look at the menu first so that when you sit down you can immediately order. Hey, when you ask for the menu, use the QR receipt, then when youre seated you can scan the QR. Hard copy menu? There are no spares, only a few are said to be used at all. Is there a menu on IG? Theres no menu on IG either, he said OK, maybe its still new so the SOP and service are still a mess. Can be repaired again. So that the order process can be faster. OK, continue, the place matches the reviews of food bloggers on IG, you can find it yourself, its a good place The food. The one I ordered was around 50k-70k We ordered pasta and fish n chips to make it quick. And apparently, it came out quickly About 10-15 minutes the food came out. There was one that was stuck and only came out 25 minutes after ordering. Gtw, why bother with it, yes, the name is also hype, its still normal. Three Ways Garlic pasta with Grilled Chicken. The portion of pasta is large and not stingy   The garlic really tastes good but its not bitter, suitable for those who love garlic The Grilled Chicken is delicious The Fish n Chips are delicious, the fish portions are big too.   The tartar sauce also tastes just right, okay. Pasta Carbonara, the same as the previous one, lots of pasta portions, eggs A little bit is too salty for me, but since its a childs meal, Id like it to be creamy and salty As for the food, at this price its delicious, full and satisfied The drink was a bit disappointing hehe. Order Chocolate and Matcha Latte. Iced. In the menu description it says it tastes RICH. So my expectations are high with a price of almost 40k hehe. Its delicious, it tastes good, but its not rich. The chocolate is less medok, the Matcha is also less mushy. So I was a bit disappointed in the drinks. Maybe I should have ordered the coffee menu, maybe its guaranteed to be delicious because they specialize in coffee. Overall GOOD, I will eat here again if I go to Ocean Park BSD again. Oh yes, there are additional pluses and minuses. Plus, there is hand sanitizer on each table, there are coffee bean decorations on the glasses which make the table smell nice, tissues are available The downside is that the staff at the table cleaning department just told me to wash the cloth used to wipe the table more often, because when I first sat down at the table it smelled like a dirty cloth that I rarely checked. The one I used just wiped it off and on but didnt wash it, so the smell stuck to the table. Hopefully it will be better on my next visit.

review_text: The Honeycomb Latte was great. The design of this cafe is super cool. Great lighting, clean area, and super fast crews. A very makes sense price. Also because of the poor crowd management, I would not recommend this cafe as a cafe that you can have a slow talk with your friends.

review_text: Satu kata untuk menggambarkan tempat ini adalah NYAMAN. Begitu masuk tempat ini kita akan disuguhkan dengan ruang yang tertata sangat apik, resik, dan teratur. Meskipun hanya terdapat sekitar 10-15 meja, tapi suasanya benar-benar nyaman. Untuk sekedar menikmati hidangan yang tersedia (baik kopi, non kopi, atau menu cake dan yang lainnya), maupun berkumpul bersama teman atau keluarga. Menu yang tersedia sangat sesuai baik dari sisi harga maupun rasa. Pelayanan yang ramah tak luput jadi nilai positif tempat makan ini. Bahkan, toiletnya tak absen dari apiknya sang owner dalam menjamin kebersihan dan kerapihan demi kepuasan pelanggan. Mungkin saja tantangan bagi pemilik tempat ini adalah  karena tempatnya yang kecil, sehingga (mungkin) pada saat jumlah pengunjung banyak, dibutuhkan strategi baik dari sisi pengaturan parkir kendaraan maupun pengaturan tempat duduk. Overall, good job Sugar Bloom Atelier.

Friendly service cannot fail to be a positive value of this place to eat. In fact, the toilet is not absent from the owners neatness in ensuring cleanliness and tidiness for customer satisfaction. It is possible that the challenge for the owner of this place is because the place is small, so (perhaps) when the number of visitors is large, a strategy is needed both in terms of vehicle parking and seating arrangements. Overall, good job Sugar Bloom Atelier.

review_translated_text: Randomly coming home from a wedding party wanting something sweet, I came across Sugar Bloom, I often pass by but I dont know if there is a place here that sells cakes. I ordered 4 menus, all of them were the best, no regrets. Gluten free orange is really delicious, not too sweet and fresh because there are orange pieces in it so its not bad, this is the overall winner in my opinion. These smores brokies are sweet but not overpowering, theres marshmellow in them so they add texture and its not boring, eat this while its warm so it melts. As a drink, I ordered peach tea and citrus pop, both were really refreshing!

Several times crossing this Kedai, because of the location right at the traffic lights junction, from Anggrek loka residences to Eka Hospital, BSD. From outside, the Kedai looks cozy, shady by the trees, with spacious parking lot. They have two seperated rooms; indoor and outdoor. If you re a smoker, you choose the outdoor. Unfortunetely,  they dont provide wifi for customers, yet, only for internal usage only, but i see some plugs at the indoor room, so you can bring your gadget for fun or work here, at least. The foods and beverages are good. We order their two main dish; mie laksa and kwitiau. The two are not disappointed for us, also the lime squash and kopi tarik, for the drinks. They also have a quite big sign board outside, when we entering this Kedai from the main door: Halal. So, for moslem likes us, this one definitely importent. Will we come back again? Yes, why not, the place is nice, the foods, drinks are delicious, not so far from our home. A place we can try to work, or having a meeting with client or friend in Tangerang Selatan area. review_text: Assalamualaikum warahmatullahi wabarokaatuh,, Selamat sore semua semoga kita senantiasa diberi kesehatan dan keselamatan dimanapun kita berada. Sore ini saya berkesempatan mengulas tempat atau restoran starbucks intermark serpong yang kebetulan saya pernah singgah disini wkwk Tempatnya tidak terlalu luas namun sangat cocok untuk nongkrong bareng teman ataupun keluarga. Tempatnya bersebelahan dengan hotel Swiss yang mana sering berlalu lalang keluar masuk kendaraan motor dan mobil. Suasananya ramai sekali kali dilihat dari luar,, tapi kali kita berada didalam starbucks nya lumayan hening dan tidak terlalu terganggu oleh bisingnya kendaraan. Tempatnya sangat strategis bangunannya pun sangat minimalis sehingga terasa nyaman untuk singgah walau sejenak. Menunya pun lengkap dari mulai makanan ringan dan berat sekali pun ada disini. Dari segi minuman juga lengkap sekali mulai dari rasa buah-buahan sampai rasa kue juga ada disini kayaknya wkwk Pelayanannya sangat ramah dan sangat antusias terhadap pengunjung. Menunggu pesanan jadi pun tidak terlalu lama karena barista juga tidak sendirian bekerja tapi dibantu oleh rekan kerja lainnya. Tersedia wifi gratis juga,, tapi kita harus membeli produk terlebih dahulu baru mendapat sandi wifinya wkwk So buat kalian yang penasaran silahkan aja datang ke tempatnya,, cocok banget buat santai-santai sambil menunggu apa yang harus ditunggu wkwk Vegetarian options: Banyak varian makanan vegetari kalo kalian mau Dietary restrictions: Diusahakan jangan terlalu banyak makan kalo lagi diet wkwk Parking: Kalo masalah tempat parkir kita bisa masuk ke area hotel dan terjun ke lantai bawah dan disitu ada tempat parkir berbayar. Kid-friendliness: Kalo untuk anak-anak bisa dikondisikan oleh orang tua Wheelchair accessibility: Ada parkir khusus kursi roda juga
review_translated_text: Assalamualaikum warahmatullahi wabarokaatuh,, Good afternoon everyone, may we always be given health and safety wherever we are. This afternoon I had the opportunity to review the Intermark Serpong Starbucks restaurant which I happened to stop by hahaha The place is not too big but it is very suitable for hanging out with friends or family. The place is next to a Swiss hotel where motorbikes and cars often pass by. The atmosphere was very busy when seen from outside, but when we were inside Starbucks it was quite quiet and not too disturbed by the noise of the vehicles. The location is very strategic, the building is very minimalist so it feels comfortable to stop by even for a moment. The menu is complete, from light to heavy meals, which are available here. In terms of drinks, they are also very complete, from fruit flavors to cake flavors, they are also available here, I think The service is very friendly and very enthusiastic towards visitors. Waiting for the finished order doesnt take too long because the barista doesnt work alone but is assisted by other colleagues. Free wifi is also available, but we have to buy the product first before getting the wifi password, hahaha So for those of you who are curious, please come to the place, its really suitable for relaxing while waiting for what you have to wait for hahaha Vegetarian options: There are many variations of vegetarian food if you want Dietary restrictions: Try not to eat too much if youre on a diet hahaha Parking: If there is a problem with parking, we can enter the hotel area and go downstairs and there is a paid parking area. Kid-friendliness: For children, it can be conditioned by parents Wheelchair accessibility: There is dedicated wheelchair parking too

review_text: Area Loka65 di Anggrek Loka udah mulai banyak toko2 yang buka. Salah satunya Lattetude ini. Area coffeeshop ini ada 2 lantai; lantai 1 lebih banyak dipakai untuk area dapur jadi indoor area hanya ada 2 meja dan outdoor 1 meja. Sedangkan lantai 2 nya lebih luas dan ada colokan di setiap mejanya Menunya juga cukup lengkap; makanan berat, dessert, snack, kopi maupun non-kopi. Sayangnya, waktu main ke sini, staffnya terlalu berisik  Padahal di area lantai 2 cukup PW untuk WFCan. _ Review based on our visit in March 2023 Follow us on IG/TT @ngopidiserpong

We really hope you will come back again soon and witness our improvement. Regards, Lattetude Management
review_translated_text: The Loka65 area in Anggrek Loka has started to have lots of shops opening. One of them is Lattetude. This coffeeshop area has 2 floors; The first floor is mostly used for the kitchen area, so there are only 2 tables in the indoor area and 1 table in the outdoor area. Meanwhile, the 2nd floor is wider and there are plug sockets at every table The menu is also quite complete; heavy meals, desserts, snacks, coffee and non-coffee. Unfortunately, when we played here, the staff was too noisy  Even though the 2nd floor area has enough PW for WFCan. _ Review based on our visit in March 2023 Follow us on IG/TT @ngopidiserpong

review_text: BSD Awalnya cuma  cap cip cup  cari cafe bt nunggu anak latihan basket di daerah sini. Eh ternyata enak loh.. gak nyangka Berhubung perut lagi kosong, langsung lah pesen makanan rada berat yang biasanya kalo makan di cafe tuh ya rasanya  so-so  aja. Mie kocok jadi pilihan pertama. Eh taunya enak. Coba lagi bakwan pake bumbu kacang, eh enak juga.. lanjut siomay bandung, mantep pisan euy.. haha.. Yg agak kurang sih cirengnya ya.. teksturnya terlalu halus, kurang  gorengan abang2  padahal dipping saucenya enak, rasa manis asem pedes gitu.. Akhirnya coba desertnya, gara2 denger ada orang pesen itu  Classic tiramisunya mantep  rasa manis, kopi dan creamnya semuanya pas.. Bakal jadi langganan nih kalo ke daerah BSD

review_translated_text: BSD At first it was just cap cip cup looking for a BT cafe waiting for the kids to practice basketball in this area. Eh, it turns out to be delicious... I didnt expect it Since my stomach was empty, I immediately ordered a rather heavy meal, which usually tastes so-so when you eat at a cafe. Shaken noodles are the first choice. Eh, thats delicious. Try again the bakwan using peanut sauce, its delicious too... continued with Siomay Bandung, its really delicious... haha... Whats a bit lacking is the cireng... the texture is too smooth, its not quite fried, bro, even though the dipping sauce is delicious, the taste is sweet and spicy... Finally tried the desert, because I heard someone ordered it... The classic tiramisu is great... the sweetness, coffee and cream are all just right.. Will be a regular if you go to the BSD area

review_text: Terpaksa harus kasih bintang 2 padahal makanan dan minumannya lumayan enak2 tapi karena pelayanannya (lebih tepatnya salah satu pelayan cowoknya) bikin kita trauma untuk balik lagi kesana :(. Kami kesana hari senin 8 Mei 2023 sekitar jam 11 siang, kami datang sekitar 15org terdiri dari dewasa dan anak2, saat itu table di lantai 2 di isi oleh kami dan 1 table oleh tamu lain, ketika tamu di table sebelah kami pergi, kami request untuk menambah meja dr table sebelah mengingat jumlah kami yg banyak dan kursinya tdk cukup, tapi oleh staf yg pria tsb dibilang meja tsb sudah ada yg reservasi, dia cleaning meja sebelah kami cukup kasar terdengarnya, sapu dijatohin ke lantai dan dia teriak2 ke bawah ke temannya tanya : buat brp orang? Seolah2 kami pikir orangnya sudah waiting list di bawah, tapi hingga kami pulang, meja sebelah kami tetap kosong dan table di bawah pun kosong semua, isi resto hanya kami dan info dari staf yg cewek saat itu (untuk staf cewek ada saat itu super ramah pelayanannya) bilangnya meja sebelah kami kosong tdk ada yg reservasi ketika kami minta tolong dia untuk foto kami. Please jgn sampai krn 1 oknum bikin tamu pada kabur dan males balik lagi, semoga ke depannya pelayanannya bisa lebih baik lagi. Thanks
response_from_owner_text: Halo Kak Surayya Lutfi, Kami dari Team Lattetude memohon maaf yang sebesar-besarnya atas ketidaknyamanan yang telah kakak dan rekan-rekan alami. Kami telah melakukan investigasi dan mendapatkan konfirmasi bahwa staff kami sama sekali tidak bermaksud sebagaimana yang kakak dan rekan-rekan rasakan. Namun dengan alasan apapun, staff kami dan seluruh team Lattetude tetap meminta maaf atas hal ini dan kami pastikan hal tersebut tidak akan terulang kembali. Untuk itu sebagai permintaan maaf, kami sudah siapkan Voucher khusus untuk menyambut kedatangan kakak berikutnya. Kakak bisa menghubungi email kami di Lattetudebsd@gmail.com untuk klaim Voucher tersebut. Terima kasih banyak atas perhatian dan waktunya, review dari kakak akan kami jadikan semangat untuk terus memperbaiki pelayanan kami. Salam Lattetude Team
review_translated_text: We were forced to give 2 stars even though the food and drinks were quite delicious, but the service (more precisely, one of the male waiters) made us traumatized to go back there :(. We went there on Monday 8 May 2023 at around 11 am, we came with around 15 people consisting of from adults and children, at that time the table on the 2nd floor was filled by us and 1 table by another guest, when the guests at the table next to us left, we asked to add a table from the table next to us considering there were so many of us and there werent enough chairs, but by The male staff said that the table already had a reservation, he was cleaning the table next to us quite rudely, he dropped the broom on the floor and he shouted downstairs to his friend asking: for how many people? As if we thought the people were already waiting on the waiting list downstairs, but until we went home, the table next to us was still empty and the tables below were all empty, the rest of the restaurant was just us and information from the female staff at that time (the female staff there at that time was super friendly, the service was super friendly) they said the table next to us was empty, no one had a reservation when we ask him to help us with our photos. Please dont let 1 person make guests run away and be lazy about coming back, hopefully in the future the service can be even better. Thanks
response_from_owner_translated_text: Hello Sis Surayya Lutfi, We from Team Lattetude apologize profusely for the inconvenience that you and your colleagues have experienced. We have carried out an investigation and received confirmation that our staff did not mean what you and your colleagues felt. However, for whatever reason, our staff and the entire Lattetude team still apologize for this and we ensure that this will not happen again. For this reason, as an apology, we have prepared a special voucher to welcome your next sisters arrival. You can contact our email at Lattetudebsd@gmail.com to claim the voucher. Thank you very much for your attention and time. We will encourage your review from you to continue improving our services. Regards Lattetude Team

review_text: Lokasi deket bgt Eka Hospital. Kesini awalnya asal masuk aja krn dari luar terlihat nyaman. Ternyata makanan dan minumannya OK!!! Pas kesana pesen es kopi susu kampung,  kopi susu butter, dimsum dan cireng. Es kopi susu kampungnya menurutku sih B aja ya kayak kopi susu pd umumnya, tapi aku suka krn gak terlalu strong. Untuk kopi susu butternya juaraaa! Enakkk, rasanya tuh unik sulit dijelaskan. FYI utk kopi susu butter cuma bisa hot ya krn dia butternya model dimelted ke kopinya, favoritos! Lupa foto krn langsung abis diminum wkwk. Dimsumnya so so lah. Tapi cirengnya enak gak terlalu berminyak, bumbunya jg pas. Recommended utk tempat hangout atau work from coffee di daerah BSD. Oh ya saran aja mungkin utk sound musicnya bisa agak diperkecil volumenya, biar lebih nyaman kalo mau ngobrol atau sambil kerja. Soalnya pas kesana soundnya menurutku terlalu kencang. Overall, this place is recommended!
review_translated_text: The location is very close to Eka Hospital. At first I just came in because it looked comfortable from the outside. It turns out the food and drinks are OK!!! When I was there, I ordered iced kampung milk coffee, butter milk coffee, dimsum and cireng. I think the villages iced milk coffee is just B, like milk coffee in general, but I like it because its not too strong. The butter milk coffee is a winner! Its delicious, the taste is unique, its hard to explain. FYI, buttermilk coffee can only be hot because the butter is melted into the coffee, favoritos! Forgot to take a photo because I just finished drinking it haha. The dimsum is so so. But the cireng is delicious, not too oily, the seasoning is just right. Recommended for a hangout or work from coffee place in the BSD area. Oh yes, just a suggestion, maybe the volume of the music could be lowered a bit, so its more comfortable if you want to chat or work. Because when I got there, the sound was too loud in my opinion. Overall, this place is recommended!

review_text: Makanan minuman enak. Dia group nya Sei Tapi ya, pantes sei nya enak. Saya pesen Bubur daging, dagingnya pake sei. Unik sih, oke juga. Porsi mengenyangkan. Pesen juga Kopi susu butter. Ini enaaaaakkkkk.. ga terlalu strong kopinya, ada rasa butternya tapi ga ganggu, malah bikin creamy gurih gitu. Enak deh. Temen2 icip juga bilang enak. Pesen juga Buttericano kalo ga salah. Americano dg campuran syrup sesuatu. Ada rasa yg aneh sih, not for americano lovers. Padahal ini menu yg ada tanda    nya, tp menurutku lebih enak Kopi susu butter. Pesen Roti sarikaya juga lumayan enak, ga terlalu manis, gurih asinnya berasa. Cocok buat sarapan. Cobain juga Bihun gulai ayam punya temen. Rasanya lebih ke kari daripada gulai sih. Berempah tapi light ga mahteh. Tempat enak ada indoor outdoor. Kita dateng pas baru buka jam 7 (which a point plus banget buka pagi), menu udah lengkap tapi ac belom dingin. Parkir aman krn pagi, ada tarif 4000. Kalo siang rame banget sih parkiran sini.
review_translated_text: Delicious food and drink. Hes from Seis group. But yes, no wonder his Sei is good. I ordered beef porridge, the meat uses sei. Its unique, okay too. Filling portions. Also order butter milk coffee. This is great... the coffee isnt too strong, it has a buttery taste but its not annoying, it actually makes it creamy and delicious. Thats delicious. Friends who have tasted it also said it was delicious. Also ordered Buttericano if Im not mistaken. Americano mixed with something syrup. There is a strange taste, not for Americano lovers. Even though this is the menu that has the    sign on it, I think butter milk coffee is better. The sarikaya bread order was also quite delicious, not too sweet, it tasted deliciously salty. Suitable for breakfast. Also try a friends chicken curry vermicelli. It tastes more like curry than curry. Spiced but light, not delicious. Nice place, indoor and outdoor. We came when it just opened at 7 (which is a plus point because it opens early), the menu was complete but the AC wasnt cold yet. Parking is safe because its morning, theres a fee of 4000. Parking here is really busy during the day.

review_text: Parkirannya mesti rebutan dengan baby shop sebelah. Awalnya iseng saja nyari tempat nongkrong sembari nunggu istri belanja keperluan bayi Menunya menarik. Bubur, kopi dan sei. Spesifik Tempatnya ada vibe jadul peranakan. Interior sebagian besar didominasi perabot kayu. Sei sapi 30k. Porsi pas (cenderung kecil), tapi setara harga. Beberapa daging agak alot chewy. Sambal matah ga terlalu pedas, tapi wangi. Berasa seperti ada penggunaan liquid smoke, tapi ga sampai mengganggu. Ada bayam crispy on the side Es susu tape. Ini menarik. Perpaduan susu, gula aren dan tape ketan. Bisa request tingkat manis Donat. 20k utk 3pcs. Agak berminyak Roti srikaya. Ini juara sih. Wangi margarin terasa. Tekstur crispy luar dan soft di dalam. Srikaya juga ga terlalu tebal, jadi ga overly sweet Pintu toilet ga bisa ngunci But overall, its a good dining experience
review_translated_text: You have to fight for parking with the baby shop next door. At first I was just looking for a place to hang out while waiting for my wife to shop for baby needs The menu is interesting. Porridge, coffee and sei. Specific The place has an old school Peranakan vibe. The interior is mostly dominated by wooden furniture. Sei cow 30k. Portions are just right (tend to be small), but worth the price. Some of the meat is a bit chewy. The sambal matah is not too spicy, but fragrant. It feels like liquid smoke is being used, but its not annoying. Theres crispy spinach on the side Ice milk tape. This is interesting. A combination of milk, palm sugar and sticky rice tape. Can request sweetness level Donuts. 20k for 3pcs. A bit oily Srikaya bread. This is a winner. You can feel the smell of margarine. The texture is crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. Srikaya is also not too thick, so its not overly sweet The toilet door couldnt lock But overall, its a good dining experience

review_text: Sempet bingung waktu nyari Kedai Bintang Terang, lokasinya berada di ruko seberang Eka Hospital. Namun, tulisan kedai-nya tidak terlalu terlihat. Makanan utama gw pesan Nasi Se i Sapi. Yang gw suka dari Se i Sapi-nya dia kayanya pakai daun bayam goreng tepung. Gw suka banget crispy food, tapi sayang beberapa dari daun bayam goreng tepungnya sedikit melempem. Se i sapinya cukup enak, chilli oil nya pedas tapi sedikit terlalu asin buat gw. Makanan kedua, Nasi Gule Sapi. Ini enak, kuahnya terasa, daginya masih pakai slice yang mirip dengan Se i Sapi. Habis makan lanjut kerja, jadi harus sambil ngemil. Cemilan gw pesan Cireng, untuk persausan dikasih sepertinya saus rujak. Sausnya tidak terlalu pedas. Namun, untuk Cirengnya sendiri sedikit hambar menurut gw, walalupun sudah ditaburi bubuk bumbu. Minuman pendamping, seperti biasa perkopian. Gw pesan Es Kopi Susu Kampung. Rasanya cukup enak tapi kopinya kurang terasa. Tempatnya cukup nyaman untuk sambil ngobrol atau WFC. Beberapa spot disediakan sofa, jarang banget gw liat kedai Se i menyediakan sofa. Nasi Se i Sapi (3/5) Nasi Gule Sapi (3/5) Cireng (2/5) Es Kopi Susu Kampung (3/5) Parking: Parkiran sering penuh, sering diarahkan untuk parkir bahu jalan. Namun, tidak rekomendasi karena bisa saja diderek. Kid-friendliness: Tersedia high-chair namun terbatas. Wheelchair accessibility: Tidak dapat menggunakan kursi roda.
review_translated_text: I was confused when looking for Kedai Bintang Terang, the location is in the shophouse opposite Eka Hospital. However, the shop writing is not very visible. My main dish was Nasi Sei Beef. What I like about Sei Sapi is that it uses flour-fried spinach leaves. I really like crispy food, but unfortunately some of the fried spinach leaves are a little soggy. The beef sei is quite delicious, the chili oil is spicy but a little too salty for me. Second food, Nasi Gule Beef. This is delicious, the sauce tastes good, the meat still uses slices similar to Sei Sapi. After eating, I go to work, so I have to snack. For snacks I ordered Cireng, for the sauce I was given something like rujak sauce. The sauce is not too spicy. However, the Cireng itself is a little bland in my opinion, even though it is sprinkled with spice powder. Complementary drink, as usual coffee. I ordered Iced Kopi Susu Kampung. The taste is quite good but the coffee doesnt taste enough. The place is comfortable enough for chatting or WFC. Some spots provide sofas, its very rare for me to see Sei shop providing sofas. Sei Beef Rice (3/5) Beef Gule Rice (3/5) Cireng (2/5) Kampung Milk Iced Coffee (3/5) Parking: Parking lot is often full, often directed to parking on the side of the road. However, it is not recommended because it could be towed. Kid-friendliness: High-chairs are available but limited. Wheelchair accessibility: Cannot use a wheelchair.
